Manage cluster linking mirror topics.

Usage:
  confluent kafka mirror [command]

Available Commands:
  create            Create a mirror topic under the link.
  describe          Describe a mirror topic.
  failover          Failover mirror topics.
  list              List mirror topics in a cluster or under a cluster link.
  pause             Pause mirror topics.
  promote           Promote mirror topics.
  resume            Resume mirror topics.
  reverse-and-pause Reverse local mirror topics and pause remote mirror topics.
  reverse-and-start Reverse local mirror topics and start remote mirror topics.

Global Flags:
  -h, --help            Show help for this command.
      --unsafe-trace    Equivalent to -vvvv, but also log HTTP requests and responses which might contain plaintext secrets.
  -v, --verbose count   Increase verbosity (-v for warn, -vv for info, -vvv for debug, -vvvv for trace).

Use "confluent kafka mirror [command] --help" for more information about a command.
